                            <comment id="12435936" author="army" created="Tue, 19 Sep 2006 18:15:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch that does the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 1. Updates the 2200M message text to be more generic,&lt;br/&gt;
    as suggested in the description of this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 2. Replaces &quot;see next exception&quot; with the in-lined &lt;br/&gt;
    error message while continuing to do exception&lt;br/&gt;
    chaining as usual.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 3. Also replaces &quot;see next exception&quot; with in-line&lt;br/&gt;
    error messages for a couple of other SQL/XML&lt;br/&gt;
    errors--namely UNEXPECTED_XML_ERROR and&lt;br/&gt;
    XML_QUERY_ERROR.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran xmlSuite on Windows 2000 using ibm142 and all tests passed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NOTE: This patch has a one-line conflict with the patch posted for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1772&quot; title=&quot;Error 42Z78 &amp;quot;Failed to locate &amp;#39;Xalan&amp;#39; API  classes&amp;quot; should not have sqlstate class &amp;#39;42&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1772&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1772&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  When either patch is committed, the other will have to be regenerated to resolve the conflict.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
