                            <comment id="12436259" author="army" created="Wed, 20 Sep 2006 16:34:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for committing the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1772&quot; title=&quot;Error 42Z78 &amp;quot;Failed to locate &amp;#39;Xalan&amp;#39; API  classes&amp;quot; should not have sqlstate class &amp;#39;42&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1772&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1772&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch (and the &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1776&quot; title=&quot;ERROR 42Z72: XML syntax error; missing keyword(s): &amp;#39;AS&amp;#39;. - Misleading text&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1776&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1776&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch, as well!), Mike.  I&apos;m attaching a new patch for this issue that resolves the conflict with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1772&quot; title=&quot;Error 42Z78 &amp;quot;Failed to locate &amp;#39;Xalan&amp;#39; API  classes&amp;quot; should not have sqlstate class &amp;#39;42&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1772&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1772&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  I applied the patch and ran xmlSuite on Windows 2000 (ibm142) with no failures.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
